Detailed Description

Namespace for the Image Processing Library (ipl) system.

This prevents nameclash with classes from other libraries.

Format is: 

                        Dimensions: w h
                        x0y0 x1y0 x2y0 ...
                        x0y1 x1y1 x2y1 ...
                        ...

Where w is width of array and h is height. Note: Due to problems with Visual C++ 6.0 and Borland 5.0 with template classes and friend functions, the definition needs to be in the header declaration, it helps a bit (but not in all cases) to bypass the bugs.
